### PHP Form Email Validation

Email validation ensures users provide properly formatted email addresses.

### Using filter_var

The most reliable way to validate an email in PHP:

```php
<?php
$email = "user@example.com";
if (filter_var($email, FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL)) {
    echo "$email is a valid email address";
} else {
    echo "$email is not a valid email address";
}
?>
```

### Complete Email Validation

```php
<?php
$email = $emailErr = "";

if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") {
    if (empty($_POST["email"])) {
        $emailErr = "Email is required";
    } else {
        $email = trim($_POST["email"]);
        // Remove all illegal characters
        $email = filter_var($email, FILTER_SANITIZE_EMAIL);
        // Validate
        if (!filter_var($email, FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL)) {
            $emailErr = "Invalid email format";
        }
    }
}
?>
```

### Validation Methods

| Method | Description | Reliability |
|--------|-------------|-------------|
| `filter_var()` with FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL | Built-in validation | High |
| Regex pattern | Custom pattern matching | Medium |
| DNS check | Check if domain has MX records | Additional |
| Send confirmation email | Verify ownership | Highest |

### Regex Alternative

```php
<?php
if (preg_match("/^[\w.-]+@[\w.-]+\.\w{2,}$/", $email)) {
    echo "Valid email";
}
?>
```

> **Key Point:** `FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL` follows the RFC standard for email validation and is the recommended approach.
